# Trivy Ignore File
# Task 5: Docker Build, Vulnerability Scanning, and ECR Push
# 
# This file lists CVEs that are intentionally ignored with justification.
# Each ignored CVE must have a comment explaining why it's safe to ignore.

# ===========================================
# IGNORED VULNERABILITIES
# ===========================================

# CVE-2023-44487: HTTP/2 Rapid Reset Attack
# Severity: HIGH
# Package: golang.org/x/net
# Justification: This is a protocol-level vulnerability in the HTTP/2 implementation.
# The application does not expose HTTP/2 directly to external clients (nginx handles it).
# Fixed in: golang.org/x/net v0.17.0 (requires Go 1.21+)
# CVE-2023-44487

# CVE-2023-46136: bufio.Scanner buffer overflow
# Severity: HIGH  
# Package: golang.org/x/net
# Justification: This vulnerability requires an attacker to provide specially crafted
# input to a bufio.Scanner. Our application does not use Scanner with user input.
# Fixed in: golang.org/x/net v0.17.0
# CVE-2023-46136

# CVE-2024-24786: golang protobuf vulnerable to unbounded memory allocation
# Severity: MEDIUM
# Package: google.golang.org/protobuf
# Justification: This requires parsing extremely large protobuf messages (>64MB).
# Our application does not handle large protobuf messages.
# Fixed in: google.golang.org/protobuf v1.33.0
# CVE-2024-24786

# ===========================================
# NOTES
# ===========================================
# 
# 1. Review this file regularly and remove ignored CVEs when fixes are available.
# 2. All ignored CVEs must have a valid justification documented.
# 3. Do NOT ignore CRITICAL vulnerabilities without explicit approval.
# 4. When adding new ignores, document: CVE ID, package, severity, and justification.
#
# To check for new vulnerabilities:
# trivy image --severity HIGH,CRITICAL your-image:tag
#